This PR adds two macros to the project: `fn_selector!()` and `calldata()`.
These macros simplify the usage of the `std::low_level_call::call_with_function_selector` function by providing a more convenient way to generate the function_selector and calldata arguments.

contracts/low_level_call/src/main.sw
```sw
fn call_low_level_call(
    target: ContractId,
    function_selector: Bytes,
    calldata: Bytes,
    single_value_type_arg: bool,
) {
    let call_params = CallParams {
        coins: 0,
        asset_id: BASE_ASSET_ID,
        gas: 10_000,
    };

    call_with_function_selector(target, function_selector, calldata, single_value_type_arg, call_params);
}
```
low_level_cal test
```rust
let function_selector = fn_selector!(set_value(u64));
let call_data = calldata!(42u64);

contract_instance
    .methods()
    .call_low_level_call(
        contract_id.clone().into(),
        Bytes(function_selector),
        Bytes(call_data),
        true,
    )
    .call()
    .await?;
```

